definition: acrobatic display (esp. on horseback) (old)/variant of 懈[xie4] and 邂[xie4] (old)
to divide/to break up/to split/to separate/to dissolve/to solve/to melt/to remove/to untie/to loosen/to open/to emancipate/to explain/to understand/to know/a solution/a dissection

sentences.english: They are leaving for New York tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 明天她們將次解纜前去紐約。

sentences.english: Will Sam leave for Bombay next month?
sentences.chinese: 薩姆下月將解纜前往孟買嗎？

sentences.english: He left for Beijing from a week.
sentences.chinese: 一週後他解纜去了北京。

sentences.english: The deck force unmoored with veteran ease.
sentences.chinese: 艙面船員動作熟練，輕而易舉地解纜拔錨。

sentences.english: He will leave for Beijing in a week.
sentences.chinese: 一週後他會解纜往北京。

sentences.english: Letgo lines and got clear of wharf, assisted by tug on starboard quarter.
sentences.chinese: 解纜，拖輪拖引右舷船尾，離開碼頭。

sentences.english: They cast off their boat yesterday morning.
sentences.chinese: 他們昨天上午解纜啓航。
